cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.DS

This paper discusses the types of prediction errors and potential remedies, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories as they deal with predictive systems. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also relevant as it involves building effective systems. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are less likely but still possible as they deal with error detection and correction.
